GIT & GITHUB COMMANDS — From 0 to Pro

1. Installation & Setup
git --version
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "you@example.com"
git config --global core.editor "code --wait"
git config --list

2. Create or Clone a Repository
Create a new repo
git init

Clone an existing repo
git clone <repo_url>
git clone <repo_url> <folder_name>

3. Basic File Operations
Check file status
git status

Add files
git add <file>
git add .
git add -A

Commit changes
git commit -m "message"
git commit -am "add + commit tracked files"

4. Viewing History
git log
git log --oneline
git log --graph --oneline --decorate
git show <commit_id>

5. Branching (Very Important)
Create & switch
git branch
git branch <branch_name>
git checkout <branch_name>
git checkout -b <new_branch>

Rename branch
git branch -m <new_name>

Delete branch
git branch -d <branch>
git branch -D <branch>   

6. Merging & Rebasing
Merge
git checkout main
git merge <branch>

Rebase
git checkout <branch>
git rebase main

Abort merge/rebase
git merge --abort
git rebase --abort

7. Remote Repository (GitHub)
Add GitHub remote
git remote add origin <url>
git remote -v

Push
git push origin main
git push -u origin main

Pull
git pull
git pull origin main

Fetch (download without merge)
git fetch
git fetch origin

8. Stashing (Temporary Save)
Save work
git stash
git stash save "message"

View stashes
git stash list

Apply stash
git stash apply
git stash apply stash@{2}

Remove stash
git stash drop stash@{0}
git stash clear

9. Undo, Reset & Restore
Undo last commit (keep changes)
git reset --soft HEAD~1

Undo last commit (remove files)
git reset --hard HEAD~1

Remove a file from staging
git reset <file>

Restore a file
git restore <file>
git checkout -- <file>

10. GitHub Authentication (Tokens)
Login
gh auth login

Clone using GitHub CLI
gh repo clone user/repo

11. Tags & Releases
Create tag
git tag v1.0
git tag -a v1.0 -m "version 1 release"

Push tags
git push origin --tags

12. Advanced Commands
Cherry-pick
git cherry-pick <commit_id>

Revert commit
git revert <commit_id>

Blame (see who changed each line)
git blame <file>

Clean untracked files
git clean -n
git clean -f

13. Full Git Workflow (Pro Level)
git clone <url>
git checkout -b feature_x
# work
git add .
git commit -m "feature_x done"
git pull origin main --rebase
git push origin feature_x
# create pull request on GitHub

14. Fixing Common Issues
Fix “detached HEAD”
git switch -c new_branch

Fix merge conflicts
# edit conflicted files
git add .
git commit

Fix wrong push to main
git reset --hard HEAD~1
git push origin main --force

15. Git Ignore
Create .gitignore
touch .gitignore

Typical patterns
*.log
*.pyc
node_modules/
env/
build/